5) What to look at in the output
You want to compare these parts:

Status line
Example:
	HTTP/1.1 200 OK
or
	HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found
Headers
Important ones:

	Server
	Content-Type
	Content-Length
	Connection
	Location for redirects

Body
Check:

	normal HTML page
	default error page
	directory listing
	uploaded file content

6) Good first tests against NGINX
Change the request path in the script and observe the response.

Test 1: existing page
	GET / HTTP/1.1
	Host: 127.0.0.1:8080
	Connection: close
Expected:

200 OK
HTML body


Test 2: missing page
	GET /does-not-exist HTTP/1.1
	Host: 127.0.0.1:8080
	Connection: close
Expected:

404 Not Found
NGINX error page or your custom error page

Test 3: redirect
If your config has a redirect route, test it and check:

301
302
Location: header

Test 4: POST later
For your future server, you will need:

body parsing
Content-Length
uploads

